        (157, 'The health care sector has been one of the middle areas in terms of performance this year, in fifth place, up more than 11%. But the vaccine production enthusiasm has helped a number of companies in and out of the S&P 500 (SP500) (NYSEARCA:SPY). Moderna (NASDAQ:MRNA) is up more than 430% year to date. On Tuesday, at 8 a.m. ET, Moderna CEO Stéphane Bancel will participate virtually in the Goldman Sachs 13th Annual Healthcare CEOs Unscripted Conference. The company is in the spotlight to see if it can fulfill its current COVID-19 vaccine supply agreements, while also pushing forward the non-COVID development efforts. While Moderna is still up sharply for the year, its down nearly 40% from its high of $169.86 hit in the first week of December. MRNA is moving into an important technical level after the recent selloff. Last week it moved just below its 50-day simple moving average, before bouncing back above. It had crossed above the 50-day and 100-day in early November when the vaccine rally arrived. It is currently below the 50-day SMA of $109.05 and the relative strength index is above oversold, still, at 40.91. But Moderna is overvalued at present and likely to tumble due to insider sales, Seeking Alpha Contributor Shock Exchange writes. “At the end of the day, the U.S. will likely not want to rely on only two vaccine manufacturers. I expect policy makers to make a concerted effort to get supply from AstraZeneca, Johnson & Johnson, Novavax and others. Once more suppliers enter the market for vaccines, there could be fewer sales to go around for Moderna and Pfizer.”'),
        (159, 'A weaker dollar and investors positioning for a recovery in the oil sector could support oil prices in 2021, Energy Aspects analyst Virendra Chauhan declared as crude touched multi-month highs at $49/bbl. The forecast comes as OPEC+ looks poised to cap output at current levels in February, with the group meeting via videoconference. It previously decided to raise output by 500K barrels per day in December, and agreed to meet every month to review production, following a difficult 2020. Prices ended the year about 20% below 2019''s average, weighed down by global lockdown measures, which have slashed fuel demand, as well as a price war between Saudi Arabia and Russia. Not out of the woods yet... OPEC Secretary General Mohammad Barkindo said Sunday that while crude demand is expected to rise by 5.9M barrels per day to 95.9M bpd this year, the group sees plenty of downside demand risks in the first half of 2021. "We are only beginning to emerge from a year of deep investment cuts, huge job losses and the worst crude oil demand destruction on record," he added. Total active drilling rigs in the U.S. have risen over the last six weeks, according to the latest survey from Baker Hughes. ETFs: USO, UCO, BNO, SCO, USL, DBO, USOI, NRGU, OILK, OLEM, NRGD, USAI, NRGO, NRGZ, YGRN'),
        (160, 'Ionic Brands (OTCPK:IONKF) has entered into a LOI to acquire assets of Peace, Love and Elixirs, LLC, a business of The Extraction Artists (EXA) on December 18, 2020, which includes three key licenses - manufacturing, edible license designation and a hemp processing license. Under the terms of the LOI, the Company will pay ~$600K to EXA and additional payment of cash and stock will be determined at closing of the transaction. EXA has operational history in servicing the retail market directly by providing white labelling services to some of the biggest retail chains in the Oregon market. Under the terms of the LOI, the companies will immediately move to a definitive agreement and have targeted a closing date of mid-February 2021.'),
        (161, 'TEGNA (NYSE:TGNA) and NBC announces a comprehensive, multi-year deal that renews station affiliation agreements for 20 TEGNA markets nationwide, including 10 of the top 25 markets for NBC. The 20 markets renewed cover 17% of the U.S. audience and nearly 21M households. TEGNA is the largest independent owner of NBC affiliates. Dave Lougee, president and CEO, TEGNA: “This new multi-year agreement allows our stations to continue providing consumers and advertisers with premium network content such as TODAY, Sunday Night Football and the Tokyo Olympic Games. We value our collaboration, which enables us to provide must-have national content alongside our award-winning local news, weather and sports.”'),
        (165, 'TEGNA (NYSE:TGNA) and NBC announces a comprehensive, multi-year deal that renews station affiliation agreements for 20 TEGNA markets nationwide, including 10 of the top 25 markets for NBC. The 20 markets renewed cover 17% of the U.S. audience and nearly 21M households. TEGNA is the largest independent owner of NBC affiliates. Dave Lougee, president and CEO, TEGNA: “This new multi-year agreement allows our stations to continue providing consumers and advertisers with premium network content such as TODAY, Sunday Night Football and the Tokyo Olympic Games. We value our collaboration, which enables us to provide must-have national content alongside our award-winning local news, weather and sports.”'),
        (166, 'Kaixin Auto (NASDAQ:KXIN) entered into a definitive share purchase agreement (SPA) with the shareholders of Haitaoche Limited on Dec. 31, 2020. The SPA supersedes a binding term sheet between Kaixin and Haitaoche, which was announced on Nov. 5, 2020. According to the SPA, Kaixin will acquire 100% of the share capital of Haitaoche from the Sellers. As consideration for the acquisition, Kaixin will issue an aggregate of 74,035,502 ordinary shares to the Sellers. The Company is required is apply for initial listing in connection with the Acquisition pursuant to Rule 5110(a) of the Nasdaq Stock Market. The acquisition will close by March 31, 2021. Shares +8% premarket.'),
        (167, 'AZZ (NYSE:AZZ) has acquired all the assets of Acme Galvanizing, Inc., a privately held hot-dip galvanizing and zinc electroplating company based in Milwaukee, Wisconsin. Terms of the transaction were undisclosed. The acquisition is expected to be accretive to earnings within the first year of operation. Bryan L. Stovall, President & COO of AZZ Metal Coatings, commented, "We are pleased with the synergistic acquisition of Acme, as we continue to execute our strategic plan to drive profitable growth and strengthen our overall Metal Coatings business. With the acquisition of Acme, AZZ enhances its scope of metal coating services in the Midwest with the addition of four advanced fully automated zinc plating lines and a totally enclosed galvanizing kettle. We welcome Acme''s employees and customers to AZZ and look forward to a seamless integration with uninterrupted customer service."'),
        (168, 'The U.S. casino operator MGM Resorts (NYSE:MGM) has proposed £8B (~$11B) in a bid to takeover Entain (OTCPK:GMVHF), the owner of the Ladbrokes and Coral betting brands - WSJ. However, the British gaming company says that the offer “significantly undervalues” the company. As per the proposal, investors in the U.K. group would receive 0.6 MGM shares, valuing their Entain shares at 1,383p — a 22% premium to its closing price of 1,133.5p on Dec. 31, 2020. Entain has also asked MGM to provide additional information in respect of the strategic rationale for a combination of the two companies. Shares in Entain, previouly know as GVC, jumped more than 25% when the market opened Monday, making it the biggest riser on the FTSE 100. MGM may also offer a “limited partial cash alternative” to Entain shareholders, who would own about 42% of the combined business. MGM’s shares ended the year down about 5% while Entain’s closed up around 30%, possibly in a nod to its potential as a takeover target. Contributor Tim Worstall stated Entain ''an undervalued buy'' in his article at Seeking Alpha. Speculation that MGM might move to take over Entain has grown following rival casino operator Caesars'' £2.9B acquisition of William Hill.'),
        (170, 'Wells Fargo starts off coverage on Airbnb (NASDAQ:ABNB) with an Equal Weight rating and price target of $160. Analyst Brian Fitzgerald: "We think there’s a lot to like about ABNB: a very large market; leading competitive positioning; a very strong mgmt team led by a visionary founder; a business model that has proven resilient through the COVID-19 pandemic—indeed, we believe the pandemic could drive persistent share gains for the category and ABNB; and the likelihood that ABNB can leverage its various tailwinds and moats to drive strong LT revenue and earnings growth. However, given an array of uncertainties—particularly regarding the complexion of the travel market as the pandemic recedes—and ABNB’s very strong stock performance post-IPO, we believe shares are trading near fair value." Other initiations this morning on Airbnb from Wall Street include Buy-equivalent ratings from D.A. Davidson, Baird (Outperform) and Canaccord Genuity (Buy), as well as cautious stances from Loop Capital (Hold), Barclays (Equal-weight), Credit Suisse (Neutral), Mizuho (Neutral) and Morgan Stanley (Equal-weight). Shares of Airbnb are up 2.57% premarket to $150.57. The company''s IPO was priced at $68 per share. Airbnb was one of the stocks mentioned in Seeking Alpha''s Catalyst Watch.'),
        (171, 'DPW Holdings (NYSEMKT:DPW) and Ascendiant Capital Markets, LLC have mutually agreed to terminate the At-the-Market Issuance Sales Agreement dated Oct. 2, 2020. The effective date of the termination was Dec. 31, 2020. The Company sold an aggregate of 12,582,000 shares of its common stock and raised gross proceeds of ~$39.9M through the Agreement. Shares +2% premarket. Press Release'),
        (172, 'Teledyne Technologies (NYSE:TDY) to acquire FLIR Systems (NASDAQ:FLIR) in a cash and stock transaction for ~$8B. FLIR stockholders will receive $28/share in cash and 0.0718 shares of Teledyne common stock for each FLIR share, which implies a total purchase price of $56/FLIR share. Net leverage at closing is expected to be ~4.0x adjusted pro forma EBITDA with leverage declining to less than 3.0x by the end of 2022. The company expects the acquisition to be immediately accretive to earnings, excluding transaction costs and intangible asset amortization, and accretive to GAAP earnings in the first full calendar year following the acquisition. The transaction is expected to close in the middle of 2021. Teledyne’s expects Q4 sales of ~$800M vs. consensus of $792.65M, diluted EPS in the range of $3.16-$3.19 vs. consensus of $2.74 and operating margin rate of ~17.5%. The company expects FY2020 EPS in the range of $10.30-$10.33, vs. prior outlook of $9.70-$10.00 and consensus of $9.88 expects to achieve record cash flow for Q4 and FY2020, ending the year with ~$115M of net debt. FLIR expects to meet or exceed the FY2020 guidance it provided on October 30, 2020. Previously: FLIR Systems reports Q3 results, re-initiates FY20 guidance (Oct. 30, 2020)'),
        (173, 'Dentsply Sirona (NASDAQ:XRAY) acquired Los Angeles based Byte, a rapidly growing clear aligner company in an all-cash deal for $1.04B. The transaction, adds Dentsply Sirona''s scale to its SureSmile clear aligner business and strengthens its connection with dental professionals. The combined company''s clear aligner platform is well-positioned to drive additional growth and Byte is expected to generate 2021 run-rate sales of at least $200M. Combined with the SureSmile business, which has an expected revenue run-rate of $100M by the end of 2021, Dentsply Sirona expects a combined clear aligner revenue run-rate in excess of $300M by the end of 2021. The CEO of Byte, Neeraj Gunsagar, and the existing management team will continue to operate the business. The acquisition is expected to generate Non-GAAP EPS accretion of at least 5c in 2021 and be incrementally accretive in the years thereafter. The transaction closed on December 31, 2020 and was funded with cash on Dentsply Sirona''s balance sheet. Conference call at 8:30 AM ET & presentation. Shares are up 0.7% PM.'),
