        (175, 'Urban Edge (NYSE:UE) acquired Sunrise Mall in Massapequa, New York from Unibail-Rodamco-Westfield for $29.7M plus up to $6M of additional contingent consideration. The property encompasses 1.2M square feet of retail space situated on 77 acres in Nassau County, Long Island and provides tremendous redevelopment opportunities given its scale and in-place zoning which provides for industrial and other uses. The mall is currently 65% occupied with anchor tenants and the existing trade area encompasses a dense population of ~1M people with an average household income of $125,000. Simultaneously, Urban Edge inks strategic partnership with Sagamore Hill Partners, an owner-operator affiliate of RIPCO Real Estate, and JG Petrucci, an established developer of industrial assets, as part of the acquisition and will serve as the managing member of the partnership with an 82.5% interest. Shares are down 0.3% PM.'),
        (176, 'Mogo (NASDAQ:MOGO) reports 108% M/M increase in new bitcoin accounts in December, a 60% increase in the dollar value of bitcoin traded on the Mogo platform. Net member additions accelerated by over 50% Q/Q in 4Q20. “Bitcoin’s exceptionally strong performance in 2020 – up over 300% for the year – and its growing credibility as an asset class in general continue to fuel interest in bitcoin among Canadian consumers,” said David Feller, Mogo’s Founder and CEO. “Despite this surge, the majority of Canadians do not own or have exposure to bitcoin, and Mogo is in a unique position to meet rising consumer demand and bring a new level of convenience and accessibility to bitcoin ownership.” Last month, the company announced it plans to make an initial corporate investment of up to C$1.5M in bitcoin and will consider additional investments in 2021 as it monetizes its C$17M investment portfolio. Shares up 11% premarket.'),
